sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K317032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This devicce includes BBa_K112808, the lysis device using three genes from enterobacteria phage T4: lysozyme, holin, and antiholin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yoshiyuki MURAKAMI

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112808
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Enterobacteria phage T4 Lysis Device - no promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pubmed Accession Number: NC_000866 Enterobacteria phage T4
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the lysis device using three genes from enterobacteria phage T4: lysozyme, holin, and antiholin. Various promoters can be installed with this device to control the lysis of bacteria. Antiholin has its own constitutive promoter to prevent the formation of holin multimers from basal expression. When the device is off, higher expression of antiholin compared to holin is required for better stability of the device.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: [Pcon].[Antiholin].[terminator] was assembled first, and then assembled with [T4 holin].[terminator]; Constitutive expression of antiholin is required before assembling holin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jin Huh

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112805
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Holins from T4 bacteriophage assemble together to form pores on inner membrane of bacteria allowing lysozyme to reach periplasm and degrade peptidoglycan layer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Making composite part of rbs.holin is problematic unless antiholin is expressed in bacteria together. Antiholin binds holin and inhibits the formation of holin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jin Huh

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112806
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The lysozyme from enterobacteria phage T4 degrades peptidoglycan layer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: High expression of lysozyme only is toxic to bacteria.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jin Huh

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112807
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Antiholin binds holin and prevents holin multimers from forming pores on the inner membrane of bacteria.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Higher constitutive expression of antiholin compared to the expression of holin is required for the stable lysis device.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jin Huh
